/target/
**/*.rs.bk
*.log

# rustfmt backups
**/*.orig

# Build artifacts that may sneak in
*.pdb
*.exe
*.dSYM/

# Editor / OS
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
.zed/

# Editor swap / temp / backup files
**/*.tmp.*
**/*.swp
**/*.swo
**/*~

# Cargo / flatpak vendor scratch. `just flatpak` writes
# .cargo/config.toml during the build under a trap that removes it on
# exit; the gitignore is belt-and-suspenders if a build is killed
# before the trap fires. `/vendor/` guards against an accidental
# top-level `cargo vendor` (the supported path puts the tree at
# target/flatpak/vendor).
/.cargo/
/vendor/

# flatpak-builder writes its build cache + git mirror to this hidden
# dir at the workspace root, separate from /target/.
/.flatpak-builder/

# Distro artifacts at the workspace root. `just flatpak-bundle` and
# the per-distro recipes write into target/release*/ ; these patterns
# catch artifacts that land at the root (e.g. linuxdeploy renames
# Grexa-*.AppImage in-place before we move it).
/*.AppImage
/*.flatpak
/*.deb
/*.rpm
/*.pkg.tar.zst
